						<summary>

						<p>The inscription is built in. Registers a gift of 14 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold by the assembly of Tiruvaraṅgam for offerings to the deity during the festivals in the months of Paṅguṉi and Aippasi. Mentions <hi rend="bold">Vēmbaṟṟūr</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Avaṉināraṇa chaturvēdimaṅgalam.</hi> The record is dated in the <hi rend="bold">24th year</hi> of the king.</p>						

						</summary>
